minfi quantile normalization

###STUDY A
ann450k <- getAnnotation(IlluminaHumanMethylation450kanno.ilmn12.hg19)
targets <- read.metharray.sheet("~/Downloads/methylation/GSE61107_RAW", verbose=FALSE)
rgSet <- read.metharray.exp(targets = targets)
phenoData <- pData(rgSet)


cellCounts <- estimateCellCounts(rgSet, compositeCellType = "DLPFC",
                                 processMethod = "preprocessFunnorm", probeSelect = "auto",
                                 cellTypes = c("NeuN_neg","NeuN_pos"),
                                 referencePlatform = c("IlluminaHumanMethylation450k"),
                                 returnAll = FALSE, meanPlot = FALSE, verbose = FALSE)

MSet <- preprocessRaw(rgSet) 

#densityPlot(MSet, sampGroups = phenoData$Sample_Group)
#densityBeanPlot(MSet, sampGroups = phenoData$Sample_Group)
#par(mar=c(5,5,4,2), mgp=c(2.5,1,0), cex.main=1.5, font.main="1", fg="#6b6b6b", col.main="#4b4b4b")
#DNAmArray::screeplot(rgSet)

#All samples are kept
detP<-detectionP(rgSet) # this gets the p-values
keep <- colMeans(detP) < 0.05
rgSet <- rgSet[,keep]

# remove poor quality samples from targets data
targets <- targets[keep,]
#targets[,1:5]
# remove poor quality samples from detection p-value table
detP <- detP[,keep]
#dim(detP)

#GRset.funnorm <- preprocessFunnorm(rgSet, nPCs=5)
GRset.funnorm <- preprocessQuantile(rgSet)

# ensure probes are in the same order in the mSetSq and detP objects
detP <- detP[match(featureNames(GRset.funnorm),rownames(detP)),] 
# remove any probes that have failed in one or more samples
keep <- rowSums(detP < 0.01) == ncol(GRset.funnorm) 
filter_rgSet <- GRset.funnorm[keep,]

keep <- !(featureNames(filter_rgSet) %in% ann450k$Name[ann450k$chr %in% 
                                                         c("chrX","chrY")])
filter_rgSet <- filter_rgSet[keep,]


# remove probes with SNPs at CpG site
filter_rgSet <- dropLociWithSnps(filter_rgSet)

# exclude cross reactive probes 
filter_rgSet <- maxprobes::dropXreactiveLoci(filter_rgSet)

minfi_betas = minfi::getBeta(filter_rgSet)
myList = strsplit(colnames(minfi_betas), "_", fixed = TRUE)
new_colnames = unlist(lapply(myList,function(x) x[1]) )
colnames(minfi_betas) = new_colnames 

keeprows = intersect(rownames(minfi_betas), rownames(myNorm))
minfi_subset <- subset(minfi_betas, rownames(minfi_betas) %in% keeprows)
myNorm_subset <- subset(myNorm, rownames(myNorm) %in% keeprows)
minfi_subset =  minfi_subset[ order(match(rownames(minfi_subset), rownames(myNorm_subset))), ]

densityBeanPlot(minfi_subset, sampGroups = NULL, sampNames = NULL, main = 'Quantile normalization minfi',
                pal = brewer.pal(1, "RdBu"), numPositions = 100000)

ChAMP BMIQ

densityBeanPlot(myNorm, sampGroups = NULL, sampNames = NULL, main = 'ChAMP BMIQ',
                pal = brewer.pal(8, "Dark2"), numPositions = 100000)

Compare the first sample

minfi_df = as.data.frame(minfi_subset[,2])
colnames(minfi_df)[1] = 'beta'
minfi_df$package = 'minfi'

champ_df = as.data.frame(myNorm_subset[,2])
colnames(champ_df)[1] = 'beta'
champ_df$package = 'champ'

betaDists<- rbind(minfi_df, champ_df)
ggplot(betaDists, aes(beta, fill = package)) + 
  geom_histogram(alpha = 0.5, aes(y = ..density..), position = 'identity')

ks.test(minfi_subset[,2], myNorm_subset[,2])
## 
##  Two-sample Kolmogorov-Smirnov test
## 
## data:  minfi_subset[, 2] and myNorm_subset[, 2]
## D = 0.21943, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: two-sided
cor(minfi_subset[,1], myNorm_subset[,1])
## [1] 0.9918521

myDMP_minfi <- champ.DMP(beta = minfi_subset, pheno=phenoData$Sample_Group, compare.group=c("SCZ","N"), adjPVal=.05,arraytype = "450K")

##       Contrasts
